dc:description: Reddish clay with slightly worn dark brown glaze.  Broken top of lamp.  Plain rim remains on one side, divides at neck of nozzle and ends in volute which is partially missing. Two circular grooves between rim and discus.  Most of discus intact.  Europa seated facing left on bull proceeding to left, her right hand on its neck, veil forming canopy over her head. Details are indistinct.  Part of head of bull missing.
